 Scenario: Project list reads canonical records not directory names\n    30\t    Given an initialized workspace with projects \"alpha\" and \"beta\"\n    31\t    And \"alpha\" is the active project\n    32\t    When the user runs \"project list\"\n    33\t    Then the output includes \"alpha\" marked as active\n    34\t    And the output includes \"beta\" not marked as active\n    35\t    And each entry shows flow, status, and name from canonical records\n    36\t\n    37\t  # SC-PROJ-005\n    38\t  Scenario: Project show displays explicit data\n    39\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    40\t    When the user runs \"project show alpha\"\n    41\t    Then the output includes flow \"standard\", prompt hash, created timestamp, run summary, and rollback summary\n    42\t\n    43\t  # SC-PROJ-006\n    44\t  Scenario: Project show resolves active project when no ID given\n    45\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    46\t    When the user runs \"project show\"\n    47\t    Then the output includes project \"alpha\" marked as active\n    48\t\n    49\t  # SC-PROJ-007\n    50\t  Scenario: Project delete succeeds when no active run\n    51\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" and no active run\n    52\t    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    53\t    Then the command succeeds\n    54\t    And the project directory \"alpha\" no longer exists\n    55\t    And \"project list\" does not include \"alpha\"\n    56\t\n    57\t  # SC-PROJ-008\n    58\t  Scenario: Project delete clears active-project pointer if selected\n    59\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    60\t    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    61\t    Then the command succeeds\n    62\t    And the active-project pointer is cleared\n    63\t\n    64\t  # SC-PROJ-009\n    65\t  Scenario: Project delete fails when project has active run\n    66\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" that has an active run\n    67\t    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    68\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"active run\"\n    69\t    And the project \"alpha\" remains addressable\n    70\t\n    71\t  # SC-PROJ-010\n    72\t  Scenario: Project creation is atomic\n    73\t    Given an initialized workspace\n    74\t    And a prompt file that will cause journal initialization to fail\n    75\t    When the user runs \"project create --id partial --name Partial --prompt bad-prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    76\t    Then the command fails\n    77\t    And no partial project directory \"partial\" is visible to \"project list\"\n    78\t    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n    79\t\n    80\t  # SC-PROJ-011\n    81\t  Scenario: Project create validates workspace version\n    82\t    Given a workspace with unsupported version\n    83\t    When the user runs \"project create --id x --name X --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    84\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"unsupported workspace version\"\n    85\t\n    86\t  # SC-PROJ-012\n    87\t  Scenario: Project create validates flow preset\n    88\t    Given an initialized workspace\n    89\t    When the user runs \"project create --id x --name X --prompt prompt.md --flow unknown\"\n    90\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"unknown flow preset\"\n    91\t\n    92\t  # SC-PROJ-013\n    93\t  Scenario: Project create does not implicitly select the project\n    94\t    Given an initialized workspace\n    95\t    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Alpha --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    96\t    Then the active-project pointer does not exist\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
