{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_30","type":"command_execution","command":"/run/current-system/sw/bin/bash -lc \"nl -ba /root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/tests/conformance/features/project_records.feature | sed -n '1,240p'\"","aggregated_output":"     1\tFeature: Project Records\n     2\t  Canonical project CRUD and immutable flow enforcement.\n     3\t\n     4\t  # SC-PROJ-001\n     5\t  Scenario: Project creation writes all canonical files\n     6\t    Given an initialized workspace\n     7\t    And a readable prompt file \"prompt.md\"\n     8\t    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Alpha --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n     9\t    Then the command succeeds\n    10\t    And the project directory \"alpha\" contains \"project.toml\", \"prompt.md\", \"run.json\", \"journal.ndjson\", \"sessions.json\"\n    11\t    And the project directory \"alpha\" contains subdirectories \"history/payloads\", \"history/artifacts\", \"runtime/logs\", \"runtime/backend\", \"runtime/temp\", \"amendments\", \"rollback\"\n    12\t    And \"journal.ndjson\" contains a \"project_created\" event with sequence 1\n    13\t    And \"run.json\" shows status \"not_started\" with no active run\n    14\t\n    15\t  # SC-PROJ-002\n    16\t  Scenario: Duplicate project ID is rejected\n    17\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    18\t    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Again --prompt prompt.md --flow standard\"\n    19\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"already exists\"\n    20\t    And the existing project \"alpha\" is unchanged\n    21\t\n    22\t  # SC-PROJ-003\n    23\t  Scenario: Flow is immutable after project creation\n    24\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    25\t    Then \"project.toml\" for \"alpha\" contains flow \"standard\"\n    26\t    And there is no CLI or store path to change the flow after creation\n    27\t\n    28\t  # SC-PROJ-004\n    29\t  Scenario: Project list reads canonical records not directory names\n    30\t    Given an initialized workspace with projects \"alpha\" and \"beta\"\n    31\t    And \"alpha\" is the active project\n    32\t    When the user runs \"project list\"\n    33\t    Then the output includes \"alpha\" marked as active\n    34\t    And the output includes \"beta\" not marked as active\n    35\t    And each entry shows flow, status, and name from canonical records\n    36\t\n    37\t  # SC-PROJ-005\n    38\t  Scenario: Project show displays explicit data\n    39\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" using flow \"standard\"\n    40\t    When the user runs \"project show alpha\"\n    41\t    Then the output includes flow \"standard\", prompt hash, created timestamp, run summary, and rollback summary\n    42\t\n    43\t  # SC-PROJ-006\n    44\t  Scenario: Project show resolves active project when no ID given\n    45\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    46\t    When the user runs \"project show\"\n    47\t    Then the output includes project \"alpha\" marked as active\n    48\t\n    49\t  # SC-PROJ-007\n    50\t  Scenario: Project delete succeeds when no active run\n    51\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" and no active run\n    52\t    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    53\t    Then the command succeeds\n    54\t    And the project directory \"alpha\" no longer exists\n    55\t    And \"project list\" does not include \"alpha\"\n    56\t\n    57\t  # SC-PROJ-008\n    58\t  Scenario: Project delete clears active-project pointer if selected\n    59\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    60\t    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n    61\t    Then the command succeeds\n    62\t    And the active-project pointer is cleared\n    63\t\n    64\t  # SC-PROJ-009\n    65\t  Scenario: Project delete fails when