system delete partially fails after validation\n   102\t    Then the project \"alpha\" remains addressable\n   103\t    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n   104\t\n   105\t  # SC-PROJ-015\n   106\t  Scenario: Run.json contains full canonical run snapshot schema\n   107\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   108\t    Then \"run.json\" for \"alpha\" contains cycle_history, completion_rounds, rollback_point_meta, and amendment_queue fields\n   109\t\n   110\t  # SC-PROJ-016\n   111\t  Scenario: Missing project.toml fails fast with corruption error on show\n   112\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   113\t    And \"project.toml\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n   114\t    When the user runs \"project show alpha\"\n   115\t    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"missing\"\n   116\t\n   117\t  # SC-PROJ-017\n   118\t  Scenario: Missing project.toml fails fast with corruption error on list\n   119\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n   120\t    And \"project.toml\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n   121\t    When the user runs \"project list\"\n   122\t    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"missing\"\n   123\t\n   124\t  # SC-PROJ-018\n   125\t  Scenario: Missing project.toml fails fast with corruption error on delete\n   126\t    Given an initialized workspace with a project directory \"alpha\" that has no project.toml\n   127\t    When the user runs \"project delete alpha\"\n   128\t    Then the command fails with error referencing \"project.toml\" and \"missing\"\n   129\t\n   130\t  # SC-PROJ-019\n   131\t  Scenario: Project.toml records canonical copied prompt reference\n   132\t    Given an initialized workspace\n   133\t    And a readable prompt file \"external-prompt.md\"\n   134\t    When the user runs \"project create --id alpha --name Alpha --prompt external-prompt.md --flow standard\"\n   135\t    Then the command succeeds\n   136\t    And \"project.toml\" for \"alpha\" contains prompt_reference \"prompt.md\"\n   137\t    And \"project.toml\" for \"alpha\" does not reference the source path \"external-prompt.md\"\n   138\t    And \"project show alpha\" displays \"Prompt reference: prompt.md\"\n   139\t\n   140\t  # SC-PROJ-020\n   141\t  Scenario: Delete failure leaves project addressable\n   142\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" and no active run\n   143\t    When the filesystem delete fails after the project has been moved to a trash path\n   144\t    Then the project \"alpha\" remains addressable at its canonical path\n   145\t    And the active-project pointer is unchanged\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
