not contain any runtime log entries\n    33\t\n    34\t  # SC-RUN-005\n    35\t  Scenario: Run tail shows durable history only by default\n    36\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    37\t    When the user runs \"run tail\"\n    38\t    Then the output includes durable history (journal events)\n    39\t    And the output does not include a runtime logs section\n    40\t\n    41\t  # SC-RUN-006\n    42\t  Scenario: Run tail --logs appends runtime logs after durable history\n    43\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" selected as active\n    44\t    And project \"alpha\" has runtime logs\n    45\t    When the user runs \"run tail --logs\"\n    46\t    Then the output includes durable history section\n    47\t    And the output includes a runtime logs section after the durable section\n    48\t    And the durable history portion is unchanged compared to \"run tail\" without --logs\n    49\t\n    50\t  # SC-RUN-007\n    51\t  Scenario: Corrupt canonical files fail fast with file-specific errors\n    52\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    53\t    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" contains invalid JSON\n    54\t    When the user runs \"run status\"\n    55\t    Then the command fails with error referencing \"run.json\"\n    56\t    And the command does not fall back to Markdown or directory scans\n    57\t\n    58\t  # SC-RUN-008\n    59\t  Scenario: Corrupt journal fails fast\n    60\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    61\t    And \"journal.ndjson\" for project \"alpha\" contains a sequence gap\n    62\t    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    63\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"journal sequence\"\n    64\t\n    65\t  # SC-RUN-009\n    66\t  Scenario: Orphaned artifact record fails consistency check\n    67\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    68\t    And project \"alpha\" has an artifact referencing a non-existent payload\n    69\t    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    70\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"does not exist\"\n    71\t\n    72\t  # SC-RUN-010\n    73\t  Scenario: Runtime log write failures do not affect durable history\n    74\t    Given runtime log writes are failing\n    75\t    When durable history is queried via \"run history\"\n    76\t    Then durable history records are returned intact\n    77\t    And no durable history records are fabricated, removed, or reordered\n    78\t\n    79\t  # SC-RUN-011\n    80\t  Scenario: Missing run.json fails fast\n    81\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    82\t    And \"run.json\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n    83\t    When the user runs \"run status\"\n    84\t    Then the command fails with error referencing \"run.json\" and \"missing\"\n    85\t\n    86\t  # SC-RUN-012\n    87\t  Scenario: Missing journal.ndjson fails fast\n    88\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    89\t    And \"journal.ndjson\" for project \"alpha\" has been deleted\n    90\t    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    91\t    Then the command fails with error referencing \"journal.ndjson\" and \"missing\"\n    92\t\n    93\t  # SC-RUN-013\n    94\t  Scenario: Orphaned payload record fails consistency check\n    95\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\"\n    96\t    And project \"alpha\" has a payload with no matching artifact\n    97\t    When the user runs \"run history\"\n    98\t    Then the command fails with error containing \"no matching artifact\"\n    99\t\n   100\t  # SC-RUN-014\n   101\t  Scenario: Run tail includes payload and artifact records in durable section\n   102\t    Given an initialized workspace with project \"alpha\" that has payload and artifact records\n   103\t    When the user runs \"run tail\"\n   104\t    Then the durable section includes payload and artifact records\n   105\t    And the output